module main

-- Regression: deeply nested expressions must parse/elaborate without
-- overflowing the host's caller stack. Compilation.parse now runs on a
-- dedicated large-stack worker, so LIBRARY consumers (this test harness, the
-- LSP) survive pathological nesting just like the CLI (which runs its whole
-- main on a large-stack thread). Depth kept moderate because the front end is
-- currently super-linear in nesting depth (tracked perf bug).

deepValue : Int
